  "description": "Positive known-answer vectors for rfc9162-sha256 inclusion (audit) proofs per RFC 9162 §2.1.1 (proof generation) and §2.1.3.2 (proof verification). A proof is the ordered array of 32-byte sibling node hashes from the leaf level up to the root: proof[0] is the leaf-level sibling, proof[len-1] is the top-level sibling. Verification recomputes from leaf = SHA-256(0x00 || leaf_digest), folding each sibling (left child when the running node is a right child, else right child) and MUST equal root after the final fold. The single-leaf tree has an empty proof. Each case lists every leaf position. Tree 'tree-4' is the balanced split (4 -> 2+2); tree 'tree-7' exercises two levels of odd-leaf recursion (7 -> 4+3, right subtree 3 -> 2+1). Roots match the rfc9162-sha256-root-kat vectors. Every proof MUST be produced byte-identically and accepted by conforming verifiers.",
